  "summary": "Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor and Insertion of Sensitive Information Into Sent Data in Calico",
  "details": "Clusters using Calico (version 3.14.0 and below), Calico Enterprise (version 2.8.2 and below), may be vulnerable to information disclosure if IPv6 is enabled but unused. A compromised pod with sufficient privilege is able to reconfigure the nodeâ€™s IPv6 interface due to the node accepting route advertisement by default, allowing the attacker to redirect full or partial network traffic from the node to the compromised pod.",
